<div class="slide">
    <h1>The Interactive Python Interpreter</h1>
    <ul>
        <li>Lets you type code straight in</li>
        <li>Code executed immediately</li>
            <ul><li>Each line is run as soon as you press enter</li></ul>
        <li>Type 'python' in your shell</li>
        <li>Press Ctrl+D to exit</li>
    </ul>
</div>

<div class='slide'>
    <h1>Variables in Python</h1>
    <ul>
        <li>You can assign values to variables using the assignment operator</li>
        <li>In the interpreter, you can display them simply just by typing the variable name</li>
    </ul>
    <br /><center><img src='interpreter-show-variable.png' /></center>
</div>

<div class='slide'>
    <h1>Using the Interpreter as a Calculator</h1>
    <ul>
        <li>We can use the interpreter to perform simple or complex calculations</li>
        <li>Need to learn about <a target='new' href='../basic-concepts/simple-numbers.html'>Numbers</a></li>
        <li>First, we want to try out some <a target='new' href='interpreter-exercises.html#simple'>simple calculations</a></li>
        <li>Then some <a target='new' href='interpreter-exercises.html#advanced'>slightly more difficult calculations</a></li>
